3. The method of claim 2, wherein the adjusting the power of the pilot signal comprises:
setting the power of the pilot signal to a first power level;
increasing the power of the pilot signal to a second power level in response to a mobile device being determined to have attached to the femto cell access point device;
storing the power of the pilot signal at the second power level in response to the mobile device being determined to have remained attached; and
resetting the power of the pilot signal to the first power level in response to the mobile device being determined to have detached from the femto cell access point device.

10. The method of claim 9, wherein the set of femto cell access point devices is a first set of femto cell access point devices, and further comprising:
identifying a second set of femto cell access points that share a cell identification report data representing channel conditions for a set of femto cell devices corresponding to the second set of femto cell access points;
refining the second set of femto cell access point devices resulting in a refined set of femto cell access point devices;
identifying a femto cell access point device in the refined set of femto cell access point device to serve a subscriber station for which a transfer from a macro network device to the femto cell access point device is requested; and
facilitating the transfer requested for the subscriber station and the femto cell access point device.

12. A system, comprising:
a processor that facilitates execution of instructions stored in a memory to perform operations, comprising:
tracking attachment events from a macro cell device to a femto cell device;
generating a schedule for gating a pilot signal of a femto cell device using the attachment events;
increasing a power of the pilot signal according to a first slope defined by the schedule;
decreasing the power of the pilot signal according to a second slope defined by the schedule;
verifying the first slope and the second slope satisfy a defined slope function defined to mitigate induced interference conditions in a wireless environment in which the femto cell device operates; and

a transmitter, configured to transmit a pilot signal power profile of the femto cell device using the schedule.

26. The system of claim 25, wherein the operations further comprise:
identifying the other femto cell devices that share the common identifier based on a radio link condition for a set of femto radio access network devices;
utilizing the plan to refine membership of the other femto cell devices resulting in a refined set of femto cell devices;
identifying a serving femto cell device in the refined set of femto cell devices to serve a wireless device that requests a transfer from a macro network device to a femto cell network device; and
resolving a handover associated with the transfer between the wireless device and the serving femto cell device.

32. The non-transitory computer-readable storage medium of claim 30, the operations further comprising:
establishing a plan to reuse the usage schedule in connection with a set of femto cell access point devices;
identifying a subset of the set of femto cell access point devices that share a cell identification based at least in part on a received channel conditions report for the subset of femto cell access point devices;
utilizing the plan to identify a refined set of femto cell access point devices that is a subset of the set of femto cell access point devices;
identifying a serving femto cell access point device from the refined set of femto cell access point devices to serve a subscriber station that requests a transfer from a macro network device to a femto network device; and
establishing a connection between the subscriber station and the serving femto cell access point device.
